&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt; 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;Thanks to David and Rob for the input. Dave is right, JFCUnit is not 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;100% the same as having a person use the keyboard and mouse. 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;Instead, JFCUnit tries to get reasonably close and make the test code 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;easy to develop and maintain. Hopefully this will make it easier for 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;teams to write GUI tests and therefore test more than they could in 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;the past. 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt; 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;Maybe JFCUnit could have an option to use Robot for creating the 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;events. Why don&#39;t you add it as a feature request? 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt; 
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&gt;- Greg 
